[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run against the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness triggered an [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mASan[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m heap-buffer-overflow in the `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction of the libexif library. The crash occurred during a multi-byte read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m just past the end of a heap allocation when processing malformed EXIF [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The fuzzer report indicates a memory safety violation: a heap-buffer-overflow [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected by AddressSanitizer.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations and Findings  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash is reproducible via the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness, which calls [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` on arbitrary input.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • ASan reports the overflow origin in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during a `memcpy` call.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The invalid read accesses [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting exactly at the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap buffer.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The stack trace shows the call chain:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy`  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry`  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content`  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data`  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data`  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Heap allocation was performed by libFuzzer’s test harness, not by application [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic. The harness merely provides the entry point for fuzzed data.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Shadow byte dump confirms the one-byte overflow immediately past the allocated [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To understand the full scope of this overflow, the following code sections should[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe reviewed:  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • exif-data.c around line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m in `exif_data_load_data_entry` – the exact `memcpy`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvocation and its buffer bounds assumptions.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The logic in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnear [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlines [0m[1;36m531[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m984[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that compute data lengths and offsets prior to copying.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation strategy for EXIF data buffers in `exif-data.c` and any metadata[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing routines that determine entry sizes.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness in `exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`, to confirm how inputs are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed into `exif_data_new_from_data` but noting the harness is not itself faulty.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis report identifies a concrete heap-buffer-overflow in libexif’s data-loading [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic when consuming untrusted input via the fuzzer entry point.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [32m%u in '%s'."[0m[39m, i, [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m515[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  exif_ifd_get_name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mifd[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m516[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m517[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m518[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m519[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Unknown tag 0x%04x [0m[32m([0m[32mentry %u in '%s'[0m[32m)[0m[32m. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mPlease report this tag "[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m520[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"to [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m<libexif-devel@lists.sourceforge.net>."[0m[39m, tag, i,[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m521[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  exif_ifd_get_name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mifd[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m522[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->options & [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF_DATA_OPTION_IGNORE_UNKNOWN_TAGS[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m523[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m524[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m525[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mentry = exif_entry_new_mem [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->mem[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m526[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m527[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  exif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF_LOG_CODE_NO_MEMORY, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m528[0m[39m:                                          [0m[32m"Could not allocate memory"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m529[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  return;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m530[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m531[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, entry, d, ds,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m532[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m   offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m * i[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m533[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_content_add_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->ifd[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mifd[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m534[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_entry_unref [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m535[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mbreak;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m536[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap-buffer-overflow occurs in [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call. Although the code has checks `doff < size`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `s <= size - doff`, it computes both `doff` and `s` as [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit unsigned ints. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen `entry->components` or `format size` is large, the multiplication `s = [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * components` can overflow [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m bits, resulting in a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrapped-around small `s` that passes the check but actually overruns the buffer. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSimilarly, casting the [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit data offset from the EXIF “external data” field into [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man unsigned int without overflow protection can produce a `doff` that is out of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds in practice but still passes `doff < size` due to wrap-around or truncation.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The symptom is a one-byte [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor multi-byte[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m read just past the allocated region,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered by malformed EXIF entries crafted by the fuzzer.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Critical Logic to Preserve  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing logic for parsing inline data versus “external” data offsets [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` vs. `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` branches[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanity checks that reject entries where the tag data lies past the end of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe provided buffer.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging and “skip-entry” behavior for invalid or unknown tags: we must [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to skip bad entries rather than abort or change parsing order.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The behavior of `exif_tag == MAKER_NOTE`, including storing `offset_mnote`.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Proposed Patches in [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the types of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from `unsigned [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint` to `size_t` to allow full [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit arithmetic on [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit platforms.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. **Prevent integer overflow** when computing `s`:  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Before `s = format_size * components`, check if `components > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat_size > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m components`. If so, log a debug message and return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskip[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. **Up-convert the EXIF “external data” offset** safely:  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Read the [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit offset into a `uint32_t raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massign `doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Replace existing bounds checks with size_t-safe versions:  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `doff > size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39muse cast: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `s > [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Proceed with `entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `memcpy` only after[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthese strict guards.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Steps to Implement  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In libexif/exif-data.c, locate `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Change declarations at the top of the function:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • Replace `unsigned int s, doff;` with `size_t s, doff;`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. After computing `entry->format` and `entry->components`, insert:  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `uint32_t fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `uint32_t comp = entry->components;`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomp != [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && fmt_size > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m comp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • &nbsp;&nbsp;`[0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`[0m[32m"Entry component count * format size [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32moverflow"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • &nbsp;&nbsp;`return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mfmt_size * comp;`  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. For the “external data” branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, read the raw offset then cast:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `uint32_t raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;`  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Else: `doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Replace the existing sanity checks with:  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        • `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Leave the rest of the function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallocation, memcpy, MakerNote logic[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification and Side-Effect Mitigation  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By using `size_t` for all buffer-length arithmetic and explicitly checking for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow before multiplying, we guarantee that `s` always reflects a valid, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon-wrapped size. This eliminates the out-of-bounds read in `memcpy`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve all parsing logic, logging, and skipping. Valid EXIF data [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences remain unaffected.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes are made to the fuzzing harness or any tests; invalid entries are [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply skipped rather than overflow-copied.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential side effect: entries with extremely large component counts or format[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizes will now be skipped [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlogged and ignored[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This matches the safety-first [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprinciple for malformed inputs and is preferable to memory corruption.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Re-run the `exif_from_data_fuzzer` harness and confirm the ASan crash no [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlonger occurs.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Run existing libexif regression tests to ensure no valid EXIF images are [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincorrectly rejected.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review code coverage to confirm the overflow guard is exercised by fuzzed [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run against libexif’s `exif_from_data_fuzzer` triggered an [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry`. The overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs when copying up to [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes from a computed data offset that sits just past [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation. A patch was applied in `libexif/exif-data.c`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Change the types of local variables `s` and `doff` from `unsigned int` to [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size_t`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Add an explicit overflow check for `format_size * components`.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Refine bounds checks on `doff` and `s` against the buffer `size`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Update debug logging to use `%zu` for `size_t`.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen re‐running the fuzzer on the same testcase, the same ASan heap-buffer-overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `exif_data_load_data_entry` persisted at the same source location, indicating [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch did not prevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invoked `exif_data_new_from_data`, which in turn called [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` on an input blob of length [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inside `exif_data_load_data_entry`, the code computes the field data size `s = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat_size * components` and the data offset `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39meither an inline offset or a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer into the blob[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A later `memcpy` reads `s` bytes from `d + doff` without adequately ensuring [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff + s <= size`.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan reports a read of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at offset [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly one past the allocated region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[1;36m180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m24f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, causing the crash.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow happens on a multi-byte read [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`__asan_memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not a single-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccess.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The bug reproduces consistently on a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte testcase, suggesting a specific [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed EXIF entry with small inline size and out-of-bounds offset.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The call stack points to line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of `exif-data.c` in unpatched code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mshifted to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m220[0m[39m after the patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Lines changed in `exif-data.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround the entry loader routine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `unsigned int s, doff;` → `size_t s, doff;`  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Wrapped the multiplication `[0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * components` in a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck against `SIZE_MAX` to prevent overflow, returning early if invalid.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Changed how `doff` is derived: always cast to `size_t`, split inline vs. [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal data paths.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Strengthened bounds checks:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Updated debug messages to use `%zu` for size_t.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and re-running the fuzz target, ASan still reports the same [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow at the updated line[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing the same testcase.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPost-patch log snippet  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- ASan summary remains a “heap-buffer-overflow” in `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The offending address and allocation region are identical, showing that neither [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow check nor the type changes prevented the [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read past the buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace through `exif_data_load_data_content` and up to [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` is unchanged.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The computation of `doff`, especially for inline entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhen `s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`; verify that `offset` itself is validated.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Handling of entry types and component counts in `[0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` vs. [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`entry->components`, ensuring no malformed tags slip through.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code path that chooses between inline vs. external data—specifically whether [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge offsets in the external case [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are checked against both `size` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many TIFF/EXIF directory boundaries.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` that [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterates entries and may influence the `offset` parameter passed into [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Overall, the metadata parsing routines in `exif-data.c` around lines [0m[1;36m150[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m250[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be audited to ensure all integer operations and pointer arithmetic stay [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin the buffer bounds before any multi-byte reads.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m426[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m427[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_CORRUPT_DATA, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m428[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u+2 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, ds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m429[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m430[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m431[0m[39m:    [0m[39mn = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m432[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m433[0m[39m:    [0m[39m          [0m[32m"Loading %hu entries..."[0m[39m, n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m434[0m[39m:    [0m[39moffset += [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m435[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m436[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Check if we have enough data. *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m437[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m*n[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m438[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mn = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mds - offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m439[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m440[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Short data; only loading %hu entries..."[0m[39m, n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:974[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m983[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m974[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* IFD [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m offset *[0m[35m/[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m975[0m[39m:    [0m[39moffset = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m976[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m977[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"IFD 0 at %i."[0m[39m, [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m978[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m979[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ds is restricted to [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bit above, so offset is restricted too, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m should not overflow. *[0m[35m/[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m980[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > ds || offset + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m > ds[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m981[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m982[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m983[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Parse the actual exif data [0m[1;39m([0m[39musually offset [0m[1;36m14[0m[39m from start[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-format.[0m[1;92mc:65[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m74[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:unsigned char[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m66:e[0m[39mxif_format_get_size [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifFormat format[0m[1;39m)[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:     [0m[39munsigned int i;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:     [0m[39mfor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; ExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.size; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:     [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.format == format[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:     [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn ExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.size;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:     [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root‐cause analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   After the recent “size_t” rewrite in exif_data_load_data_entry, the two bounds [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   should in principle prevent any [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from overrunning the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer’s [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   However, the real problem is that the “size” argument passed into [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry is not the true remaining length of the buffer at pointer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39md – it is the original TIFF block length, not the length after skipping the EXIF [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader. In practice the code does:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Read the TIFF IFD0 offset at byte [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m of the blob  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Call [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, IFD0, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m,  ds,  offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   i.e. it advances d by [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskipping the EXIF header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but still passes the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfull ds [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as “size”. That means d actually points to a [0m[1;36m201[0m[39m-byte region, but the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloader believes it has [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes. A malformed tag whose data-pointer field raw_off [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m= [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m will pass the two bounds checks [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[39m < [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m? false ⇒ check1 skipped; [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m ≤ [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m−[0m[1;36m207[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m? false ⇒ check2 skipped[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and fall through into memcpy, landing exactly at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of the region. ASan then reports the [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte out-of-bounds read at offset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch outline  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In exif_data_new_from_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m980[0m[39m in libexif/exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, change [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe call that invokes exif_data_load_data_content to pass the correct “size” for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe truncated buffer: subtract the initial header bytes that were skipped from the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtotal ds. For example, if the code currently reads:  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, IFD0, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds,    offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     replace it with:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, IFD0, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures “size” now matches the actual bytes available at pointer d.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Review any subsequent recursive calls in exif_data_load_data_content [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExifSubIFD, thumbnail data, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm they always invoke the loader with a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer + offset pair whose “size” argument reflects “total buffer minus that [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset.” If they do e.g.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, ifd1, d, ds, sub_offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     then it is correct to keep ds constant, because offset tells the entry loader [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhow many bytes to skip. But if any call passes a sliced pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + sub_offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout adjusting ds, mirror the same “size = ds – sub_offset” fix there.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – By correcting the size parameter at the top level, all downstream size checks [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdoff ≥ size, s > size − doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m become accurate for the true data slice.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – No change is made to the harness or fuzzer logic. We only touch libexif’s [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing functions.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – We preserve existing behavior for valid EXIF files [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize – [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m is larger than [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many legitimate TIFF block offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and only reject malformed tags whose data [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer lies outside the true buffer.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – The `size_t`‐based overflow and component‐count guards remain in place and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontinue to prevent integer multiplication overflow.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – This approach is minimal, does not alter tests, and aligns with how the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitial call to the IFD parser must reflect the real slice length.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Potential side effects & mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – Under these new checks, certain old malformed testcases that previously [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturned “success” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbut silently read past the EXIF header area[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will now correctly[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe dropped. No legitimate image will break because valid offsets and sizes in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell‐formed EXIF files always lie within the ds – [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m region.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   – To be sure, add a libexif unit‐test that invokes exif_data_new_from_data on a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmall buffer of size [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m bytes and confirms it does not crash.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/24/25 21:26:33][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=569907;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=254829;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m3[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.VULNERABLE[1m)[0m                                   [2m               [0m
[2;36m[12/24/25 21:29:36][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.ANALYZE -> TeamStatus.[1;33mPATCH[0m                     ]8;id=607466;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=746679;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m3[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.VULNERABLE[1m)[0m                                   [2m               [0m
[2;36m[12/24/25 21:30:23][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.[1;33mPATCH[0m -> TeamStatus.EVALUATE                    ]8;id=839457;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=153270;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
