[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmp33h_3dhd[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run against libexif’s exif-data.c revealed a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry: a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation. A [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was applied in exif-data.c to change integer types [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom `unsigned int` to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size_t`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add an overflow guard on `format_size * components`, adjust the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomputation of the data offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, tighten bounds checks using the new size [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypes, and modify the call to `exif_data_load_data_content` by adding a flag. [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRe-running the fuzzer after the patch still produces the same ASan [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at roughly the same location, indicating the patch did not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer invocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives `exif_data_new_from_data`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich in turn calls `exif_data_load_data_content` and then [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, during a `memcpy` from source data `d` into an `entry` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The failure log shows a multi-byte read starting exactly at the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytes [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, into byte [0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m, offset [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey observations in the initial log  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `s = format_size * components` and `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are both `unsigned int`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- There is a check for `s < entry->components` or `s == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, but no proper check for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minteger overflow or zero-component cases.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, `doff` is read from the buffer unvalidated; otherwise it’s set to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Bounds checks compare `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` using `unsigned [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mint`, but these did not prevent the out-of-bounds [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed the types of `s` and `doff` to `size_t`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Inserted an explicit overflow guard before computing `s`:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  uint32_t fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  uint32_t comp     = entry->components;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomp == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || fmt_size > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m comp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Entry component count * format size overflow"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mfmt_size * comp;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Computed `doff` with explicit casts:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      uint32_t raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Updated both bounds checks to use `size_t` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff >= [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize` and `s > [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and adjusted log format specifiers to `%zu`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Modified the call site in the Exif header parsing to:[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, EXIF_IFD_0, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, offset, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;39m([0m[39madded a flag argument[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer run after patching still reports the same heap-buffer-overflow in [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, now at line [0m[1;36m220[0m[39m after the insertions.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The ASan stack trace, allocation size, and shadow memory layout are virtually [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The exact computation of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal byte count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vs. actual data length available [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the buffer, especially for component formats larger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The derivation and interpretation of `doff` from in-buffer offsets, including [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether the raw offset should be adjusted by any header or base pointer.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between the Exif header skip [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`offset`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`flag` parameters passed to `exif_data_load_data_content` and [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All paths into `exif_data_load_data_entry`, including handling of different IFDs,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure every code path validates `doff + s` against the total input size.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mexif_from_data_fuzzer[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reapply and preserve the correct parts of the previous patch:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep `s` and `doff` as `size_t`.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain the overflow guard for computing `s = fmt_size * comp`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Retain the change in format specifiers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`%zu`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for logging `size_t` values.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Revert the unintended change to the call‐site of `exif_data_load_data_content`:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Change back the last argument [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrecursion cost[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from `[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m` to the original `[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, strengthen bounds checks [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround both:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Reading the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte “value offset” [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`raw_off`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Copying the actual data via `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Concretely:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after computing `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe total byte count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert a check that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensures the entry header and offset field lie entirely within the buffer:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure we have at least [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes of entry header: tag+format+components *[0m[35m/[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  [0m[32m"Entry header past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 8 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Then, before fetching `raw_off` for `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, or before pointing at inline data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor `s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, verify that the subsequent bytes to be read exist:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Need [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes at offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m for [0m[32m'value offset'[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      [0m[32m"Value offset past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 8 + 4 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         uint32_t raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inline data sits at offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, with up to [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes *[0m[35m/[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwe already know offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m <= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Finally, before the `memcpy`, collapse the two original sanity checks into a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle unified guard that ensures the entire `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39md + doff, d + doff + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` range lies [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin the buffer:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure data block [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff .. doff+s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is within buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove or disable the previous two separate checks:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     in favor of the single `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The root cause is that the code reads the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte “value offset” from `d + [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` without first verifying that those bytes exist, and similarly may call [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` with an out-of-range source pointer when `doff + s` computes to beyond [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size`.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By inserting explicit checks for `[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <= size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor external [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m <= size` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor inline data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we prevent any [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read even when a malicious or malformed offset is present.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Collapsing the two old checks into one [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff + s <= size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simplifies the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic, ensuring that no single byte of the requested `s` bytes falls outside the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reverting the recursion-cost flag change restores the original API behavior of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content`; that change was unrelated to the overflow and can be[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafely undone.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing functionality is preserved: entries whose `s` and `doff` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlegitimately fit in the buffer will still be loaded, error paths unchanged except [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor more precise log messages.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external library, harness, or test code is modified; this patch confines [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself to `exif-data.c` and maintains the same public API and fuzzer harness [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side effects: only minor performance cost for additional integer tests; [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigated by doing inexpensive comparisons and preserves library safety guarantees.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe OSS-Fuzz harness triggered an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif`’s exif-data loader. The failure occurs in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `memcpy` reads past an allocated buffer. A patch was applied that:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed intermediate variables to `size_t`[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added integer-overflow checks for component count and format size[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added bounds checks on the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte entry header and [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte value-offset field[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Unified the final sanity check to ensure `doff + s ≤ size`[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite these guard clauses, the same OOB read is still reported at the same [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation in `exif_data_load_data_entry`, indicating the overflow conditions are not[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfully covered by the new checks.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer run with AddressSanitizer flagged a heap-buffer-overflow in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash stack trace shows a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read at an address exactly at the end of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that the code computed a data offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or size [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuch that `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` reads beyond the provided buffer.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations in the Initial Issue  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `entry->components` and `[0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` multiply into [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`s`, but no check for overflow or maximum allowed size.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code differentiated small values [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from larger ones [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdecide whether to read data in-place or via an offset, but only tested `doff < [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize` and `s ≤ size - doff`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan log pinpoints the `__asan_memcpy` call as the crash site, confirming the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread is out-of-bounds.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The patch modifies `exif_data_load_data_entry` as follows:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Declares `s` and `doff` as `size_t` instead of `unsigned int`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wraps the size computation in a uint32 overflow check:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       uint32_t fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       uint32_t comp     = entry->components;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomp == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || fmt_size > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m comp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"... overflow"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       s = fmt_size * comp;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adds a check that `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m ≤ size` before reading the entry header.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Refines the branch for `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte header + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset *[0m[35m/[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"... out-of-bounds"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       doff    = raw_off;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consolidates bounds checking to:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mlog[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"... data block past end"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leaves the final `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` intact.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After rebuilding with the patch, the fuzzer still triggers an identical [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow at the same location [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:227[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The ASan report shows a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read starting at the end of the allocated [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion, confirming that either `s` or `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor both[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain unconstrained in some[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calculation of `s` when `entry->components` or `exif_format_get_size` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturn unexpected values [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., underflow, unexpected zero[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The branch logic for small values [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m versus large values [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure both branches enforce correct bounds.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interpretation of the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`raw_off`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: verify byte order, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignedness, and whether it needs additional validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., minimum offset, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malignment[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Overall structure of EXIF entries—particularly padding, alignment, and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple entries—to confirm that buffer reads stay within the data segment.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Internal assumptions in `exif_data_alloc` and how `size` and `doff` interact [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the total buffer length passed into `exif_data_new_from_data`.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mexif_from_data_fuzzer[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ shift[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -v TESTCASE [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m438[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mn = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mds - offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m439[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m440[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Short data; only loading %hu entries..."[0m[39m, n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Unify all size‐related types to size_t and use a robust overflow macro.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change exif_data_load_data_entry signature to:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `static int [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data, ExifEntry *entry, const[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned char *d, size_t size, size_t offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Propagate this change to its callers in exif_data_load_data_content [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchange [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mds and offset to size_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and to any forward declarations.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Introduce an initial CHECKOVERFLOW for the full [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m‐byte entry header before any [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreads. This prevents unguarded [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m‐byte or [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m‐byte reads of [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtag/format/components/value‐or‐offset:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m‐byte IFD entry is fully in [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m..size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, size, [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Entry record past end [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu+12 > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This replaces the manual `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > size` and also guards the initial [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_get_short`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`exif_get_long` calls.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. After reading `format` and `components`, guard the multiplication with a size_t [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow check:  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   unsigned char fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Unknown format size 0"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->components == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || fmt_size > SIZE_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Component×format overflow or zero"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   size_t s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mfmt_size * entry->components;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Computed data length %zu exceeds buffer %zu"[0m[39m, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Compute the data offset `doff` via two branches, each guarded by CHECKOVERFLOW: [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Inline [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte “value” field within the entry.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* inline data must fit in the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte slot and within buffer *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Inline data past end [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu+%zu > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Out-of-line [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field points elsewhere in d[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ensure the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field itself is in bounds *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, size, [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Offset field past end [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu+4 > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ExifLong raw_off = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mraw_off < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Negative data offset %ld"[0m[39m, raw_off[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      size_t doff = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mraw_off;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ensure the pointed‐to block fits entirely in d[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Data block past end [0m[32m([0m[32m%zu+%zu > %zu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Allocate and copy only after all checks pass:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!entry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   entry->size = s;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Remove all manual `offset + N > size` and `doff + s > size` arithmetic; replace [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39ma, size, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined in exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to avoid any potential [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor wrap‐around or off‐by‐one mistakes.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Update any unit tests implicitly relying on the old signature; no harness or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz logic changes.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExplanation and Justification:  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Using size_t everywhere and a single `CHECKOVERFLOW` macro guarantees no [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintermediate overflow in `a + len` or `len > size - a`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Early header‐range check safeguards the initial reads of tag/format/components [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the inline [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m‐byte “value” field.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Explicit checks for `fmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, `components == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`, and signedness of [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`raw_off` eliminate edge‐cases where malformed entries slip past the previous [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By checking `s <= size` immediately, we catch absurdly large allocations early.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This preserves existing IFD‐entry parsing logic and only tightens bounds; it does[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot modify harness, utility functions, or external libraries.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Similar patterns already exist in `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m‐byte and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m*n` checks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so this approach is consistent with the rest of the code.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPotential Side Effects and Mitigation:  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changing parameter types [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`unsigned int` → `size_t`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m requires updating all call [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msites in the same translation unit; ensure no mismatched prototypes remain.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- New checks for `fmt_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` or negative `raw_off` may cause [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreviously‐accepted [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbut semantically invalid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m files to be rejected earlier; [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhowever, this only enhances robustness against corrupt data.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Use of `CHECKOVERFLOW` must be verified to match the existing macro [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation in `exif-data.c`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReferences:  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- exif_data_load_data_content uses `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset, ds, [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m*n[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m426[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m437[0m[39m. The same pattern here [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensures uniform safety.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Typical IFD‐entry size is [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes; guarding that region prevents any OOB in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent logic.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/24/25 21:35:47][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=181714;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=832208;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
